The electoral field was being prepared in parallel. Trump used his social media platform to repeat that the 2020 election had been \'93Rigged and Stolen,\'94 urged the Justice Department to investigate again, and called for the elimination of mail-in and early voting and the imposition of strict voter ID requirements. He threatened federal intervention in the upcoming midterms and cast California\'92s Proposition 50\'97a Democratic attempt to suspend its independent redistricting commission in response to Republican gerrymanders elsewhere\'97as evidence of \'93rigging\'94 on the other side. In North Carolina, the Republican-led General Assembly, under Trump\'92s influence, targeted another Democratic seat, deepening a map that already sent ten Republicans and four Democrats to the U.S. House. Rev. William Barber and allied groups prepared lawsuits and nonviolent resistance to challenge what they called racial gerrymanders. In Indiana, the governor called a special session to redraw congressional districts mid-decade, citing the need to protect the state\'92s voice in Washington. In New York, voters of color sued over a map they said diluted Black and Latino power on Staten Island. The Justice Department\'92s Civil Rights Division, now under Trump, requested 2020 election records from Fulton County, Georgia, despite prior investigations clearing the county, raising fears that federal civil rights tools were being turned into instruments of political revisionism.\
